+4.1.1.  Architectural Routing and Multiplexing
+
+   Each Endpoint associates a SCHC Instance with the corresponding PPP
+   connection. The PPP connection itself serves as the Discriminator that
+   the logical Dispatcher on the Endpoint uses to route incoming packets
+   to the appropriate SCHC Instance. The Dispatcher intercepts incoming
+   PPP packets with Protocol 0x0057 (IPv6) and dispatches them to the
+   associated Instance for decompression, or forwards native IPv6 packets
+   directly to the network stack if no rule matches.
